<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4751309>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 15. Inferiolabiata labiata. (a) Fragment displaying dactylopores with spine absent due to erosion and craters resulting from ruptured ampullae. (b) Fragment displaying abcauline dactylopore spines and longitudinal coenosteal canals.(c) Coenosteal texture. (d) Gastrostyle. (e) Pentagonal gastropore. (f) Remains of dactylostyles." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4751309/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4751307>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 14. Inferiolabiata labiata. (a) Fragment bearing flattened branches. (b) Incipient colony attached to fragment of B. candida, bearing polychaete. (c) Basal section of colony attached to B. candida, bearing polychaete." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4751307/files/figure.png" .

